Evidence Mapping for Gen-AI Ethical AI & Continuous Monitoring

## **Requirement 1: Responsible AI Principles**
- **Source**: [Microsoft Responsible AI Principles](https://www.microsoft.com/ai/responsible-ai)  
- **Section to Capture**: *“Our approach to responsible AI”* section.  
- **Screenshot Instructions**: Capture first 6 lines explaining fairness, accountability, transparency.  
- **Filename**: `01-responsible-ai-principles.png`

---

## **Requirement 2: Continuous Monitoring for Fairness**
- **Source**: [Azure AI Responsible AI Transparency Note](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-services/responsible-use-of-ai)  
- **Section to Capture**: *“Mitigating harmful and unfair outputs”* section.  
- **Screenshot Instructions**: Capture first 2–3 paragraphs describing continuous monitoring and fairness safeguards.  
- **Filename**: `02-continuous-monitoring.png`

---

## **Requirement 3: Bias and Fairness Evaluation**
- **Source**: [Azure Machine Learning Responsible AI dashboard](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/machine-learning/responsible-ai-dashboard)  
- **Section to Capture**: Overview section describing bias detection, fairness metrics, and monitoring.  
- **Screenshot Instructions**: Capture first 6 lines of the dashboard overview.  
- **Filename**: `03-bias-fairness-dashboard.png`

---

## **Requirement 4: Compliance Declarations**
- **Source**: [Microsoft Compliance Offerings](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/compliance/regulatory/offering-home)  
- **Section to Capture**: Certifications relevant to AI ethics (SOC, ISO, GDPR, financial regulations).  
- **Screenshot Instructions**: Scroll to Azure certifications → Capture the relevant list.  
- **Filename**: `04-compliance-offerings.png`

---

## **Requirement 5: SOC2 Report Evidence**
- **Source**: [Microsoft Service Trust Portal](https://servicetrust.microsoft.com/) (login required)  
- **Section to Capture**: Reports → SOC Reports.  
- **Screenshot Instructions**: Log in → Navigate to SOC Reports → Capture availability of SOC 2 Type 2 report.  
- **Filename**: `05-soc2-report.png`

---

